Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery dinos; interior glazed streaky black; exterior: black-figure decoration in two friezes; from top, possibly part of man's leg, to left and part of undetermined motif at right; below, part of back and ribs of animal to left; blobs as filling ornament.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 269, no. B206)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0258) (Phase 1)
